<br>
HotSamoan says:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>wizerds get alot of advantages over the mages as it is already. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
And mages have advantages over wizards in different areas.  &lt;cough&gt; sustained dps &lt;cough&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>first of all they get to level alot faster cuz they can quad, mages no. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The mages in my guild have leveled just as fast by soloing in places i can not.  They also get into nice fast guild xp groups much easier than i.  Quadding requires very specific circumstances, and since our quadding ability has been largely negated in PoP this argument is way weak.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>they also get to travel all over the place cuz of ports, mages no. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Oh yes you can!  All you have to do is buy youself a copy of PoP and you can take yourself almost anywhere a wizard can port, and many places we cannot.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>they get to land spells on mobs (lures) that mages can not. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I do not understand why mages have such envy over the lures.  Do you know how often i have to use lures?  Yeh there is like 2 fights i can think of where i need them.  We usually use a regular old nuke.  No really!  I swear.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>they get to have powerful bane type spells that destroy targets, mages no. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
&lt;laugh&gt; Oh yes, we get to quest to get a nuke that takes 2 frelling dots EACH CAST to hit targets that regular nukes now land on.  Not to mention that those spells only work on a very few specific velious mobs anyway.  So what's the point?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>crits without AA points. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yeh, a 2% random crit.  Woopee, all it did was prove we aren't afk.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>evac, snare etc., the list is long. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Um no, the list is very very short.  Evac (better to have a druid that can buff and heal) snare (largely a moot point since most PoP mobs are IMMUNE, not to mention the fact that it is an AE snare and therefore highly undesireable to use it in many situations where it would be useful) root (again, most PoP mobs are immune to root) and stuns (guess what, most mobs are immune to stun as well.)<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and i dont even wanna go there into the manburn issue. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Good, because it has been nerfed to near uselessness.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>you get all this nice things that mages dont then you get jealous of the mages cuz mages can outdamage you with a nook by 300 pts. at 63 the wizerds have the better nooks so it evens out by far.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I do not have a problem with mages having this nuke, i have a problem with the gross inequity in availablity of our nukes in comparison.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and saying about how you have to pay 20K or whatever for spells, you dont HAVE to pay anything, you could camp for it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The only one we can camp is sunstrike and it is a VERY rare drop off any mob that can be single grouped.  The only place it drops at a reasonable rate is VP, which is old content that requires a significant key quest timesink, and guess what, no guilds are willing to devote that kind of time just to get wizards sunstrike.  EER can NOT be camped, it requires a raid force for any of the mobs it drops off, and GSS requires killing frelling Emp. Srra!  Good luck camping that, much less buying on the open market. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>cuz everyone who gets a copy is gready and wants alotta pp for it, thats not a game issue thats a people issue.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
They want a lot of plat for it because it is extremely rare and a pain in the ass to aquire.  Those are game issues.<br>
<br>
Noonie says:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>my point is this. <br>
if almost all mages can get sofb and maelstrom of electricity, and almost all druids can get moonfire,<br>
why should only 10ish % of level 60 wizards have gss and/or eer? that makes absolutely no sense to me. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It's even worse than that.  On Veeshan, i imagine all active FoH wizards have it.  I'll take a generous guess at 15.  Three wizards in my guild alliance have it.  That's it, serverwide.  We are talking very, very few wizards have GSS.  And you have FoT off a vendor.  You are right, it makes no sense, and THAT is what some of us are complaining about, not that we are angry that mages have a nice nuke.  They need to put SS on a vendor, and make quests for EER and GSS.  Seriously. <p>Luxum Aeturnum &lt;Cestus Dei&gt;<br>
62 Sorceror<br>
Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10>Class Balance & Class Bugs</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

